This topic describes how to upgrade the Pivotal Application Service (PAS) for Windows tile and update the Windows stemcell.

## <a id='rotate'></a>Rotating Credentials

The PAS tile handles all of the credentials for PAS for Windows.

To rotate your credentials in PAS for Windows, re-deploy PAS and PAS for Windows by navigating to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and clicking **Apply Changes**.

##<a id='upgrade-tile'></a> Upgrade PAS for Windows

To upgrade PAS for Windows:

1. Follow the instructions [Upgrading PCF Products](../customizing/upgrading-products.html#other-products) with the latest PAS for Windows product download from [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/products/pas-windows).

1. If necessary, configure the product. For more information about configuring PAS for Windows, see the [Installing and Configuring PAS for Windows](./installing.html) topic.

1. Locate the **Pending Changes** section on the right-hand side of the screen and click **Apply Changes**.

##<a id='upgrade-stemcell'></a> Upgrade the Windows Stemcell

1. Navigate to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard**.

1. Retrieve the stemcell by following the steps below for your IaaS:
    * For vSphere, you must [build your own stemcell](https://github.com/cloudfoundry-incubator/bosh-windows-stemcell-builder/blob/master/create-manual-vsphere-stemcells.md).
    * For AWS, GCP, and Azure, navigate to the **Stemcells for PCF (Windows Server)** section of [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/products/stemcells-windows-server).

1. Click the **PAS for Windows** tile.

1. Within the **Settings** tab, click **Stemcell** on the left-hand navigation.

1. Click **Import Stemcell**.

1. Select the previously acquired stemcell and click **Open**.

1. Click **Installation Dashboard** to navigate back to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard**.

1. Click **Apply Changes**.

